<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Santa Monica College</h2>
<strong>Santa Monica, CA</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Students may be allowed advanced credit at the time of admission for College Board Advanced Placement (AP) Exams with scores of 3, 4, or 5 (4 or 5 for English 1). Students must submit an original copy of the Candidate Grade Report to the Admissions and Records Office. AP credit can be used toward the AA degree and for IGETC and GE Certifications.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.smc.edu/catalog/2002_2003/012_catalog_part1.htm" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

 <p class="box-padding-3">
    Additional restrictions and requirements may apply to the policy listed below. For more detailed information, visit the college's AP policy on the Web or contact the college directly.
 </p>

